Probably a bunch.

00:02:20.270 --> 00:02:22.020
[UZAKI gasps]

00:02:22.100 --> 00:02:25.270
Well, how's my form looking?
Any better?

00:02:25.350 --> 00:02:28.850
[SAKURAI] Hm... Honestly, you're
only doing slightly better

00:02:28.940 --> 00:02:30.530
than you were when you started.

00:02:30.610 --> 00:02:32.200
But hey, at least you've
stopped sinking.

00:02:32.280 --> 00:02:33.700
Aw, really?

00:02:33.780 --> 00:02:35.660
[SAKURAI] Listen carefully,
when you're doing the crawl

00:02:35.740 --> 00:02:37.950
you gotta go "fwoosh"
before you follow through.

00:02:38.030 --> 00:02:39.070
What now?

00:02:39.160 --> 00:02:41.330
"Fwoosh", like you're
a sea turtle.

00:02:41.410 --> 00:02:43.830
I'm confused. Wasn't I
fwooshing just now?

00:02:43.910 --> 00:02:46.580
What you were doing was
"splooshing." Ya see?

00:02:46.670 --> 00:02:48.550
How is that different
from what I did?

00:02:48.630 --> 00:02:51.340
Seems like "splooshing" is the
same technique as "fwooshing."

00:02:51.420 --> 00:02:52.710
[SAKURAI]
It's not.

00:02:52.800 --> 00:02:54.470
A proper fwoosh
looks like that.

00:02:54.550 --> 00:02:57.180
And when you sploosh,
it looks like this.

00:02:57.260 --> 00:02:58.600
Do you get the difference now?

00:02:58.680 --> 00:03:01.850
Absolutely not. You lost
me five minutes ago.

00:03:01.930 --> 00:03:03.350
[SAKURAI]
Hmm, that's no good.

00:03:03.430 --> 00:03:05.600
There's gotta be a better
way to explain it, right?

00:03:05.690 --> 00:03:07.110
Lemme think a sec.

00:03:07.190 --> 00:03:08.730
Can I say something?

00:03:08.810 --> 00:03:09.980
Sure. What's up?

00:03:10.070 --> 00:03:11.950
