it's nothing.

00:03:12.030 --> 00:03:13.620
Probably having a brain fart.

00:03:13.690 --> 00:03:14.610
You sure?

00:03:14.690 --> 00:03:16.280
Look, forget about it.

00:03:16.360 --> 00:03:18.860
It might come off awkward
if I mention it now.

00:03:18.950 --> 00:03:21.870
It's no big deal.
Go ahead, tell me.

00:03:21.950 --> 00:03:24.370
Do you promise you won't
take this the wrong way?

00:03:24.450 --> 00:03:26.240
Yep. You have my word.

00:03:26.330 --> 00:03:29.250
So I had this funny
realization about you.

00:03:29.330 --> 00:03:30.710
[SAKURAI]
Mm-hm.

00:03:30.790 --> 00:03:32.670
Around the third or fourth
time you offered to help me

00:03:32.750 --> 00:03:35.630
with swimming lessons, I started
having distracting thoughts.

00:03:35.720 --> 00:03:37.140
[SAKURAI]
Mm-hm. Mm-hm.

00:03:37.220 --> 00:03:40.220
I noticed how awesome you are.
It's actually beautiful

00:03:40.300 --> 00:03:42.140
seeing the way you glide
through the water.

00:03:42.220 --> 00:03:43.640
[SAKURAI]
Mm-hm. Mm-hm.

00:03:43.720 --> 00:03:45.140
But despite all your skill,

00:03:45.230 --> 00:03:47.270
you're really not a great
teacher at the end of the day.

00:03:47.350 --> 00:03:49.520
[sobs]

00:03:49.600 --> 00:03:52.020
Hey, I'm sorry! It's not that
I mean to sound ungrateful,

00:03:52.110 --> 00:03:54.360
since you've been going out
of your way to support me!

00:03:54.440 --> 00:03:56.690
[SAKURAI sighs]
Honestly, it's okay.

00:03:56.780 --> 00:04:00.660
You're not exactly wrong, so
hearing it's hardly a surprise.

00:04:00.740 --> 00:04:02.160
I'm sorry.

00:04:02.240 --> 00:04:04.490
I wish I had more experience
making sense of this stuff.

00:04:04.580 --> 00:04:06.170
I've never had to
mentor someone before.

00:04:06.250 --> 00:04:08.710
Huh? Not even the newbies?

00:04:08.790 --> 00:04:11.460
They'd love to learn from you.

00:04:11.540 --> 00:04:13.710
[SAKURAI] Maybe, but it hasn't
happened yet and everyone

00:04:13.800 --> 00:04:16.140
who joined this year already
had swim experience.

00:04:16.210 --> 00:04:18.550
[UZAKI]
Right. Guess that checks out.

00:04:18.630 --> 00:04:20.380
[SAKURAI] Besides, I didn't
start swimming until

00:04:20.470 --> 00:04:21.970
my freshman year.

00:04:22.050 --> 00:04:25.180
[UZAKI gasps] Are you serious?
And you're already that fast?

00:04:25.270 --> 00:04:28.060
[SAKURAI] I was pretty hopeless
at first, but now I'm beginning

00:04:28.140 --> 00:04:31.810
to understand how lucky I was
to have great mentors back then.

00:04:31.900 --> 00:04:34.320
It's not easy to
coach other people.

00:04:34.400 --> 00:04:36.820
[UZAKI]
Oh yeah? So what about me?

00:04:36.900 --> 00:04:38.320
If it's such a headache
to do all that,

00:04:38.400 --> 00:04:40.400
then why are you even bothering?

00:04:40.490 --> 00:04:42.200
[SAKURAI] Because it'd be
too dangerous to leave you

00:04:42.280 --> 00:04:44.490
on your own.
You're the club manager.

00:04:44.580 --> 00:04:47.330
I can't stand by and
not lend a hand.

00:04:47.410 --> 00:04:49.160
[UZAKI]
Hm.

00:04:49.250 --> 00:04:50.710
[SAKURAI]
In any case,

00:04:50.790 --> 00:04:52.790
I might only have a year of
doggie paddling under my belt,

00:04:52.880 --> 00:04:54.550
but I can still
keep an eye on you.

00:04:54.630 --> 00:04:58.590
Don't you worry. I won't
let you drown on my watch.

00:04:58.670 --> 00:04:59.880
[UZAKI]
Mm.

00:05:01.970 --> 00:05:05.350
[UZAKI] You know, you're a
real nice guy, Sakurai.

00:05:05.430 --> 00:05:07.100
[SAKURAI]
